sentences: Alibegović was born in Gornji Vakuf, Bosnia and Herzegovina on 1 January 1962.
Alibegović was born in Gornji Vakuf, Bosnia and Herzegovina on 1 January 1962. His family hails from the village Voljice near Gornji Vakuf.
Alibegović relocated to Sarajevo as a teenager, where his interest in music began.
Alibegović released his tenth studio album Zelena in May 2008.
His eleventh studio album Blago meni (2010) was released under the record label BN Music.
Originally Alibegović was intended to record the 2011 pop rock duet "Dva jarana" with Enes Begović, but the song ended up featuring Mladen Vojičić Tifa.
He is currently signed to Grand Production.
